{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-04120/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-04120"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:41:20"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, pan, tracking"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman knocks on a closed hallway door."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04120/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-04120","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04120/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-04120"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04120/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04120/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04120/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04120/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04120/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04120/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04120/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04120/canvas/1/86471799-1d47-4449-9943-c2415c55167c","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T18:58:17.054Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The layout of the house remains a critical feature of Reynolds and Alma’s relationship. The threshold to Reynolds’s room, in particular, functions as a fulcrum where characters battle over control. Here, Alma attempts to enter his private space, and therefore enter into a closer state with him, but is denied. Immediately after, however, Cyril pushes past Alma without trouble, as she remains for Reynolds the most important female figure in his life. Later, Alma will take over as Reynolds’s wife and <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW146705062 BCX4\" href=\"https://ptannotated.com/items/phan-13005.html\"><u>mother</u></a>, as it were, in the same space—simply on <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW146705062 BCX4\" href=\"https://ptannotated.com/items/phan-12039.html\"><u>the other side</u></a> of the door.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04120/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:1077.5773889636607,283.52624495289376,568.506056527591,554.293405114401"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04120/canvas/1/4b826fe2-018e-4d16-86e3-5d83f7a8ce44","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T18:58:31.306Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Once again, Alma dons burgundy, a color associated with several key moments in her burgeoning relationship with Reynolds.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04120/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:431.5477792732167,570.3633916554509,549.1251682368775,394.0780619111712"}}}]}]}]}